WEBVTT

1
00:01:08.027 --> 00:01:09.612
<i>SUSAN: And that's the news.</i>

2
00:01:09.695 --> 00:01:14.700
But before we sign off, we'd like to
congratulate our very own Evan Baxter,

3
00:01:14.784 --> 00:01:18.579
who has just been elected
Buffalo's representative to Congress.

4
00:01:18.663 --> 00:01:21.082
- And, now, we have a surprise for Evan.
- No, you don't.

5
00:01:21.165 --> 00:01:24.543
- We do.
- Oh, no. I really didn't expect this.

6
00:01:24.627 --> 00:01:27.171
Here's a look back at his run for office.

7
00:01:27.255 --> 00:01:28.673
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

8
00:01:29.423 --> 00:01:32.260
<i>- What are we gonna do?
- ALL: Change the world!</i>

9
00:01:32.343 --> 00:01:33.344
<i>That's right!</i>

10
00:01:33.970 --> 00:01:35.471
<i>(ALL CHEERING)</i>

11
00:01:40.518 --> 00:01:42.561
<i>ALL: Baxter! Baxter! Baxter!</i>

12
00:01:49.527 --> 00:01:50.528
<i>Hi.</i>

13
00:01:50.611 --> 00:01:51.946
<i>ALL: Baxter! Baxter!</i>

14
00:01:52.029 --> 00:01:53.489
<i>That's right!</i>

15
00:01:55.741 --> 00:01:56.742
(CLEARING THROAT)

16
00:01:57.994 --> 00:02:02.206
I feel like that old Indian
in front of all the garbage.

17
00:02:03.708 --> 00:02:08.713
So, for the last time, this is Evan Baxter
for Eyewitness News. Good night.

18
00:02:09.463 --> 00:02:12.049
<i>(HAVE YOU EVER SEEN THE RAIN</i> PLAYING)

19
00:02:25.271 --> 00:02:28.482
<i>GPS: Huntsville, Virginia.
Prestige Crest, four miles.</i>

20
00:02:28.566 --> 00:02:31.193
- What did we do before GPS?
- Nothing.

21
00:02:31.277 --> 00:02:33.487
Guys, Dad's very proud of his new car.

22
00:02:33.571 --> 00:02:38.159
Hey, I am proud of my new car.
Look, I'm a politician now.

23
00:02:38.242 --> 00:02:41.162
I'm in the public eye, and as you know,
when you are in the public eye,

24
00:02:41.245 --> 00:02:42.913
image is everything, isn't it?

25
00:02:47.918 --> 00:02:50.296
EVAN: Here it is! Welcome to the good life.

26
00:02:50.838 --> 00:02:54.592
Hey, guys, why the long faces?
We're off on a new adventure!

27
00:02:55.217 --> 00:02:57.345
It's just we're going to miss our friends.

28
00:02:57.428 --> 00:02:59.263
You'll make new friends, better friends.

29
00:02:59.347 --> 00:03:00.514
Yeah, richer friends.

30
00:03:00.598 --> 00:03:04.352
Do not mouth off to me, sir.
I am the boss of you.

31
00:03:04.435 --> 00:03:07.035
And let me tell you something,
you guys are gonna love this place.

32
00:03:07.897 --> 00:03:10.737
And you know what? I think there's
something for our fishermen up there.

33
00:03:12.026 --> 00:03:14.945
EVAN: Baxter family,
this is what's called a scenic vista.

34
00:03:15.071 --> 00:03:19.033
And I don't think the big man himself
could do a better job. Pretty cool, huh?

35
00:03:19.116 --> 00:03:20.743
Hey, Dad, an iguana can stay underwater

36
00:03:20.826 --> 00:03:21.970
- for 28 minutes.
- What's that?

37
00:03:21.994 --> 00:03:23.874
- And a shrimp's heart is in its head.
- Really?

38
00:03:23.954 --> 00:03:26.235
Okay, someone's had enough Animal Planet
for one lifetime.

39
00:03:26.290 --> 00:03:28.450
Yeah, let's head out! Come on.
The best is yet to come!

40
00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:32.713
EVAN: Gentlemen,
I have saved the best for last.

41
00:03:32.797 --> 00:03:36.342
Look over to the right.
That is your new home.

42
00:03:43.724 --> 00:03:44.892
JORDAN: That's our house?

43
00:03:44.975 --> 00:03:47.120
JOAN: I don't remember it being this big
in the brochure.

44
00:03:47.144 --> 00:03:48.424
Was it this big in the brochure?

45
00:03:48.479 --> 00:03:49.730
EVAN: Pretty amazing, isn't it?

46
00:03:49.814 --> 00:03:51.399
There they are!

47
00:03:52.650 --> 00:03:55.069
Is this curb appeal or what?

48
00:03:55.152 --> 00:03:56.654
Here we go!

49
00:03:56.737 --> 00:03:59.365
- Honey, I think you're blocking my photo.
- Sorry.

50
00:03:59.448 --> 00:04:01.409
All right, everybody! Say "escrow"!

51
00:04:01.492 --> 00:04:04.328
- Escrow!
- Escrow!

52
00:04:04.537 --> 00:04:07.164
RYAN: Come on. Come on. Come on.
Come on. Go. Go. Go.

53
00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:09.708
EVAN: Guys, easy.

54
00:04:10.126 --> 00:04:11.627
(CHILDREN EXCLAIMING)

55
00:04:12.211 --> 00:04:14.004
This is our house?

56
00:04:15.297 --> 00:04:16.465
MAN: Careful!

57
00:04:16.549 --> 00:04:18.426
JOAN: Honey, be careful!
EVAN: Watch it!

58
00:04:18.509 --> 00:04:19.635
Are you kidding me?

59
00:04:19.718 --> 00:04:20.987
- Mom, can we go upstairs?
- JOAN: Yep.

60
00:04:21.011 --> 00:04:22.489
- And I get my own room, right?
- Yep.

61
00:04:22.513 --> 00:04:23.889
(YELLING EXCITEDLY)

62
00:04:23.973 --> 00:04:26.576
Mr. Baxter, could you give us some
direction on these kitchen cabinets?

63
00:04:26.600 --> 00:04:27.601
Sure.

64
00:04:27.685 --> 00:04:32.022
Okay, it's between your maple
and your old-growth Brazilian cherry.

65
00:04:32.106 --> 00:04:34.150
That is nice! Which is best?

66
00:04:34.233 --> 00:04:37.278
Well, if you're not sensitive to that
"save the rainforest" stuff,

67
00:04:37.361 --> 00:04:38.863
you can't beat the Brazilian cherry.

68
00:04:38.946 --> 00:04:40.072
It's 200, 300 years old.

69
00:04:40.156 --> 00:04:41.676
- Three hundred years.
- Three hundred.

70
00:04:41.740 --> 00:04:43.284
Wow. That is old.

71
00:04:43.367 --> 00:04:45.619
And now you are going to hold my dishes.

72
00:04:45.703 --> 00:04:47.514
- That's right. You going with the cherry?
- Cheery cherry!

73
00:04:47.538 --> 00:04:49.458
- Yeah. Definitely.
- He's going with the cherry!

74
00:04:50.249 --> 00:04:52.501
- RYAN: Dad, look!
- No, no, no!

75
00:04:52.585 --> 00:04:54.879
Ryan, do not touch him, please!

76
00:04:55.296 --> 00:04:56.839
Oh, no, no, no, no, get him away!

77
00:04:56.922 --> 00:04:59.175
No. He might have lice, fleas, maggots
or something.

78
00:04:59.258 --> 00:05:02.011
You do not play with stray dogs
because they are very...

79
00:05:02.094 --> 00:05:04.430
No, no! Get away, get away! Go!

80
00:05:05.055 --> 00:05:06.599
Okay. Oh, no, no, no.

81
00:05:06.682 --> 00:05:08.100
- He's thirsty.
- No, no, no.

82
00:05:08.184 --> 00:05:11.061
No, you don't! There we go.

83
00:05:11.145 --> 00:05:12.605
Well, Ryan, he's a stray.

84
00:05:12.688 --> 00:05:14.374
If we give him water,
he's just going to come back.

85
00:05:14.398 --> 00:05:17.776
Come on, Dad, why can't we keep him?
I mean, we've got a new house.

86
00:05:17.860 --> 00:05:19.820
Okay, Ryan, this is why we can't keep him.

87
00:05:19.904 --> 00:05:22.544
They are stinky. They are smelly.
They get hair all over the place.

88
00:05:22.615 --> 00:05:23.800
They get a little thing called the mange.

89
00:05:23.824 --> 00:05:26.869
In a nutshell, he is disgusting.
Case in point.

90
00:05:27.578 --> 00:05:29.413
(BOTH GIGGLING)

91
00:05:31.916 --> 00:05:36.837
<i>EVAN: Ladies and gentlemen, this concludes day
one of the Baxters' new and exciting life.</i>

92
00:05:36.921 --> 00:05:39.215
I have to do the new house dance.

93
00:05:39.298 --> 00:05:41.842
Wow! That dance?

94
00:05:41.926 --> 00:05:44.762
- That's a good new house dance.
- Thank you.

95
00:05:44.845 --> 00:05:47.014
You know, those boys were having
so much fun tonight,

96
00:05:47.097 --> 00:05:48.933
I thought I would never get them to bed.

97
00:05:49.016 --> 00:05:53.687
And then Ryan did the cutest thing.
He asked if we could all pray together.

98
00:05:54.146 --> 00:05:56.857
Really? What did you pray about?

99
00:05:56.941 --> 00:05:59.026
He met a dog.
What do you think he prayed for?

100
00:05:59.109 --> 00:06:00.986
(EXCLAIMING IN DISGUST)

101
00:06:01.070 --> 00:06:03.822
Just a walking petri dish, that dog.

102
00:06:03.906 --> 00:06:06.075
And Jordan was very precise.

103
00:06:06.158 --> 00:06:09.954
He prayed for good visibility, good weather
on the hiking trip tomorrow.

104
00:06:10.037 --> 00:06:13.290
The hiking trip? Oh, right. Yeah.
The hiking trip. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

105
00:06:13.374 --> 00:06:15.251
You wanna know what I prayed for?

106
00:06:15.334 --> 00:06:17.211
Yeah. What did you pray for?

107
00:06:17.294 --> 00:06:20.422
I prayed we would become closer
as a family.

108
00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:26.011
Honey, you don't need to pray for that
to happen. I will make that happen.

109
00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:27.137
(SIGHING)

110
00:06:27.596 --> 00:06:31.934
- What would you pray for?
- Me? I don't know. Praying just...

111
00:06:32.685 --> 00:06:33.727
(SIGHING)

112
00:06:33.811 --> 00:06:37.648
Honey, you're the one who said
you wanted to change the world.

113
00:06:38.148 --> 00:06:40.067
It's a pretty big job.

114
00:06:40.359 --> 00:06:43.153
If it were me,
I would take all the help I could get.

115
00:06:48.158 --> 00:06:51.263
<i>WOMAN (OVER TV): Former Buffalo News
anchor, Evan Baxter, takes office tomorrow</i>

116
00:06:51.287 --> 00:06:53.706
<i>to make good on a lofty campaign promise.</i>

117
00:06:53.789 --> 00:06:56.250
<i>- What are we going to do?
- ALL: Change the world!</i>

118
00:06:56.333 --> 00:06:59.795
<i>WOMAN (OVER TV): Good luck, Congressman.
Many have tried, many have failed.</i>

119
00:06:59.878 --> 00:07:03.048
<i>- Hello!
- This is Regina Sparks reporting for...</i>

120
00:07:06.385 --> 00:07:07.970
(SIGHING)

121
00:07:19.356 --> 00:07:20.399
(CLEARING THROAT)

122
00:07:20.482 --> 00:07:22.318
Hello, there. Hi.

123
00:07:23.402 --> 00:07:25.738
This is Evan Baxter.

124
00:07:27.323 --> 00:07:29.783
Just wanted to say thank
you for everything.

125
00:07:29.867 --> 00:07:33.662
Thank you for the new car
and for the house.

126
00:07:33.746 --> 00:07:36.707
The house is great. I love it.

127
00:07:37.374 --> 00:07:41.795
I mean, I picked it out,
but you created matter and everything, so...

128
00:07:45.299 --> 00:07:49.094
I just wanted to say that I think Joan
makes a good point,

129
00:07:49.178 --> 00:07:53.599
and that I am now in a position
of great power,

130
00:07:53.766 --> 00:07:57.645
and I know that with great power
comes great responsibility.

131
00:07:59.772 --> 00:08:01.774
So, God,

132
00:08:02.024 --> 00:08:03.025
(CLEARING THROAT)

133
00:08:05.778 --> 00:08:08.238
please help me change the world.

134
00:08:10.157 --> 00:08:12.993
Okay. That's it. I'm hanging up now.

135
00:08:13.911 --> 00:08:16.413
God bless... Well, you. Okay.

136
00:08:32.638 --> 00:08:34.390
(ALARM RINGING)

137
00:08:39.395 --> 00:08:42.648
- What? That's weird.
- What?

138
00:08:42.731 --> 00:08:44.733
I set the alarm for 7:00.

139
00:08:47.820 --> 00:08:48.821
(MOTOR WHIRRING)

140
00:08:50.948 --> 00:08:53.033
(GRUNTING)

141
00:08:54.368 --> 00:08:55.369
(SNEEZING)

142
00:08:55.452 --> 00:08:57.037
(GRUNTING)

143
00:09:18.517 --> 00:09:20.519
I am successful. I am powerful.
I am handsome.

144
00:09:20.602 --> 00:09:23.814
I am happy, successful, powerful,
handsome, happy.

145
00:09:24.356 --> 00:09:29.403
All right, everyone, wish me luck.
The Congressman has left the building.

146
00:09:29.486 --> 00:09:34.533
All right, Baxter brood, I will see you later
on this afternoon for the big hike. Yes?

147
00:09:34.616 --> 00:09:36.910
EVAN: You psyched? Are you ready?
ALL: Yeah.

148
00:09:36.994 --> 00:09:38.304
- Bye. See you.
- Good luck, honey.

149
00:09:38.328 --> 00:09:39.455
- Bye, guys!
- See you later.

150
00:09:39.538 --> 00:09:40.539
Later, gator.

151
00:09:41.498 --> 00:09:42.499
(EXCLAIMING)

152
00:09:42.583 --> 00:09:43.876
Oh, gosh.

153
00:09:43.959 --> 00:09:46.670
Wow. Honey, did you order anything?

154
00:09:47.045 --> 00:09:49.173
"Alpha and Omega Hardware"?

155
00:09:49.256 --> 00:09:51.675
- JOAN: Never heard of them.
- Me either.

156
00:09:52.009 --> 00:09:53.844
What do we have?

157
00:09:54.261 --> 00:09:55.262
(GASPING)

158
00:09:55.345 --> 00:09:57.055
What is this stuff?

159
00:09:58.474 --> 00:10:00.309
Must have the wrong address.

160
00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:02.728
Yup. The wrong address.

161
00:10:04.980 --> 00:10:06.565
WOMAN: Congressman Baxter.
Good morning.

162
00:10:06.648 --> 00:10:07.648
Good morning.

163
00:10:07.691 --> 00:10:09.085
- MAN 1: Good morning, Congressman Baxter.
- Hello.

164
00:10:09.109 --> 00:10:11.528
- MAN 2: Good morning, Congressman Baxter.
- Good morning.

165
00:10:11.612 --> 00:10:14.615
Oh, this is so cool.

166
00:10:17.826 --> 00:10:19.620
Yeah. This'll work.

167
00:10:19.703 --> 00:10:23.540
There he is! The head honcho.
The big kahuna.

168
00:10:23.624 --> 00:10:25.626
Rita, I think I have to do the dance.

169
00:10:25.709 --> 00:10:26.877
Do the dance.

170
00:10:26.960 --> 00:10:28.378
(GRUNTING)

171
00:10:30.464 --> 00:10:31.799
That's enough of the dance.

172
00:10:31.882 --> 00:10:33.967
Oh, this is nice! This is really nice!

173
00:10:34.051 --> 00:10:36.720
This is too nice.
There's something crooked going on.

174
00:10:36.804 --> 00:10:38.013
Do you smell anthrax?

175
00:10:38.096 --> 00:10:39.973
- Congressman!
- Hey, Marty!

176
00:10:40.057 --> 00:10:41.475
- Nice sound to that.
- I like it.

177
00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:42.559
Here they are!

178
00:10:42.643 --> 00:10:43.644
(ALL CHEERING)

179
00:10:43.727 --> 00:10:44.812
All right.

180
00:10:44.895 --> 00:10:46.647
You remember Sarah, Allen, Michael.

181
00:10:46.730 --> 00:10:49.459
I don't think you know the new kid
Eugene Tennanbaum. I found him at G.W.

182
00:10:49.483 --> 00:10:51.211
Sort of a walking search engine.
Watch this.

183
00:10:51.235 --> 00:10:53.487
- How many stars on the flag in 1818?
- 15.

184
00:10:53.570 --> 00:10:55.489
And Congressman Baxter's coffee habits?

185
00:10:55.572 --> 00:10:58.826
He likes a morning latte with a cruller,
a decaf espresso after lunch,

186
00:10:58.909 --> 00:11:00.494
served sans pastry of any kind.

187
00:11:00.577 --> 00:11:03.247
Very impressive.
A little freaky, but I like this kid.

188
00:11:03.539 --> 00:11:04.915
(LAUGHING) I love you.

189
00:11:07.417 --> 00:11:10.754
I mean, we should hang out socially.
I just got a ping-pong table.

190
00:11:10.838 --> 00:11:12.506
Not going to happen.

191
00:11:12.589 --> 00:11:15.843
Go find out where his license plates are.
Everybody else, back to your holes.

192
00:11:15.926 --> 00:11:18.863
- EUGENE: He was actually right.
- I'm doing a background check on that kid.

193
00:11:18.887 --> 00:11:23.559
Ta-da! This, my friend, is a power office,
to remind you of the mission!

194
00:11:23.642 --> 00:11:25.060
BOTH: "Change the world!"

195
00:11:25.143 --> 00:11:26.913
- Okay, Evan, who do you know?
- What do you mean?

196
00:11:26.937 --> 00:11:28.856
Oh, come on.
Yesterday we're in the basement.

197
00:11:28.939 --> 00:11:30.917
Today, look at this place.
It's like the Emerald City!

198
00:11:30.941 --> 00:11:34.194
"Enjoy your office.
Your neighbor, Congressman Long."

199
00:11:34.278 --> 00:11:36.363
Congressman Long did this?
Did you say "neighbor"?

200
00:11:36.446 --> 00:11:39.283
That's right. He lives in Prestige Crest,
right up the street.

201
00:11:39.366 --> 00:11:43.328
Evan, you got to tell me these things.
Think of the publicity angle on this!

202
00:11:43.412 --> 00:11:45.706
You and Congressman Long having
a barbecue.

203
00:11:45.789 --> 00:11:47.666
Congressman Long eating your hot dog.

204
00:11:47.749 --> 00:11:49.519
RITA: Hate to break up
your little weenie roast.

205
00:11:49.543 --> 00:11:52.212
Congressman Long's assistant
just dropped this off.

206
00:11:52.296 --> 00:11:53.672
The Congressman would like for you

207
00:11:53.755 --> 00:11:55.924
to junior cosponsor this bill
that he's introducing.

208
00:11:56.008 --> 00:12:00.220
Hold on. Congressman Long asked us to
junior cosponsor his bill? What's the bill?

209
00:12:00.304 --> 00:12:02.973
The Citizens' Integration
of Public Lands Act.

210
00:12:03.056 --> 00:12:05.058
Never heard of it. Gene, here, now.

211
00:12:05.142 --> 00:12:07.394
- Rita, why didn't you tell me about this?
- I just did.

212
00:12:07.477 --> 00:12:09.372
You need to tell me about it
before I need to know about it.

213
00:12:09.396 --> 00:12:11.583
- Marty, you are not the vice congressman.
- I am the legislative...

214
00:12:11.607 --> 00:12:15.235
Nobody voted for you. If Evan gets shot
in the head, you do not automatically...

215
00:12:15.319 --> 00:12:17.380
If Evan got shot in the head,
you're the first suspect.

216
00:12:17.404 --> 00:12:18.447
Play nice. Play nice.

217
00:12:18.530 --> 00:12:20.675
All right, Eugene, Congressman Long's bill.
What is it?

218
00:12:20.699 --> 00:12:23.577
HR7124, better known as CINPLAN.

219
00:12:23.660 --> 00:12:26.389
The bill would open up fringe areas
of the national parks for development.

220
00:12:26.413 --> 00:12:27.915
Long's been sitting on it for ages...

221
00:12:27.998 --> 00:12:29.958
Got it. Pause. Come on, Evan, this is huge.

222
00:12:30.042 --> 00:12:31.602
You hitch your wagon to the right star,

223
00:12:31.627 --> 00:12:33.787
you could ride all the way down
to Pennsylvania Avenue.

224
00:12:33.837 --> 00:12:35.172
This is day one.

225
00:12:35.255 --> 00:12:37.424
You got your name on a major piece
of legislation!

226
00:12:37.507 --> 00:12:40.344
And another thing,
he wants you to read it today.

227
00:12:40.636 --> 00:12:42.137
Well, I can't do it today.

228
00:12:42.220 --> 00:12:43.364
- I promised my kids...
- Eugene.

229
00:12:43.388 --> 00:12:45.432
Well, sir, there's a
time clock on the bill.

230
00:12:45.515 --> 00:12:47.601
If Congressman Long wants to pass it
this quarter,

231
00:12:47.684 --> 00:12:49.871
he's going to have to introduce it
to the committee immediately.

232
00:12:49.895 --> 00:12:52.397
I'm personally going with
whatever Congressman Baxter decides,

233
00:12:52.481 --> 00:12:55.442
because if I could be like one man,
it'd be him.

234
00:12:55.525 --> 00:12:56.860
