CONGRESSPERSON: The flood.

958
00:54:45.783 --> 00:54:47.910
This has been the hottest, driest summer
on record

959
00:54:47.994 --> 00:54:49.620
and you say we're going to have a flood?

960
00:54:49.704 --> 00:54:53.207
- When might we expect this?
- September 22, midday.

961
00:54:53.291 --> 00:54:54.292
(CROWD CHATTERING)

962
00:54:57.128 --> 00:55:00.715
- That's what I was told.
- Might I ask who told you?

963
00:55:07.555 --> 00:55:11.184
Not in front of all those people.
Don't say it. Don't say it.

964
00:55:16.481 --> 00:55:17.815
God.

965
00:55:18.441 --> 00:55:19.442
(SOBBING)

966
00:55:22.612 --> 00:55:27.325
- God? You talk to God?
- Yes.

967
00:55:27.408 --> 00:55:32.079
- LONG: And God is talking back?
- Yeah. We hung out a little.

968
00:55:32.455 --> 00:55:34.749
Well, time to update the résumé.

969
00:55:34.832 --> 00:55:37.210
Congressman, your name is being removed
from this bill.

970
00:55:37.293 --> 00:55:40.713
Obviously, the stresses of this office
have proven too much for you.

971
00:55:40.796 --> 00:55:44.091
- Please have the congressman removed.
- No. Please! You don't understand!

972
00:55:44.175 --> 00:55:46.969
God commanded me to build an ark!

973
00:55:47.053 --> 00:55:49.639
It's going to rain!
There's going to be a flood!

974
00:55:51.098 --> 00:55:55.061
- Remove him now!
- We have to prepare ourselves!

975
00:55:55.144 --> 00:55:57.855
I need to finish the ark!

976
00:55:57.939 --> 00:55:58.981
(HAMMER SLAMMING)

977
00:55:59.065 --> 00:56:01.400
Remove him now!

978
00:56:07.657 --> 00:56:10.284
Does this mean we're moving back home?

979
00:56:10.576 --> 00:56:13.329
Home, Canada. One or the other.

980
00:56:23.798 --> 00:56:28.678
Joan? I know you probably saw
what happened, but I can explain.

981
00:56:32.932 --> 00:56:36.310
Take the stuff to the car, guys.
I'll be there in a minute.

982
00:56:38.563 --> 00:56:39.689
Guys?

983
00:56:41.357 --> 00:56:42.358
(DOOR OPENING)

984
00:56:43.276 --> 00:56:48.322
I'm gonna take them to my mother's.
Evan, I think you need help.

985
00:56:48.906 --> 00:56:53.703
Joan, please. I'm not doing this.
It's not me. It's him.

986
00:56:53.786 --> 00:56:57.081
I went to that meeting in a suit,
and he took it off of me.

987
00:56:57.164 --> 00:57:00.918
Those animals are following me
because of him.

988
00:57:01.002 --> 00:57:04.630
God?
Does God know he's destroying our lives?

989
00:57:04.714 --> 00:57:07.258
Does God know
he's going to get you fired?

990
00:57:07.341 --> 00:57:09.844
Yeah! He's trying to get me fired!

991
00:57:09.927 --> 00:57:13.055
He is trying to get me fired!

992
00:57:13.139 --> 00:57:15.308
That way I'll have more time
to work on the ark!

993
00:57:15.391 --> 00:57:17.893
Because the rain
and the floods are coming.

994
00:57:17.977 --> 00:57:21.397
No, I heard you, Evan.
The whole world heard you.

995
00:57:21.480 --> 00:57:24.108
Joan, please, you gotta believe me.

996
00:57:24.191 --> 00:57:25.359
(DRIZZLING)

997
00:57:26.569 --> 00:57:31.365
There it is! It's happening!
It's happening! It's raining!

998
00:57:48.883 --> 00:57:50.384
Goodbye, Evan.

999
00:57:52.011 --> 00:57:53.012
(ENGINE STARTING)

1000
00:57:53.721 --> 00:57:54.847
Joan!

1001
00:58:03.606 --> 00:58:08.194
I know! I know. Whatever you do,
you do because you love me!

1002
00:58:15.951 --> 00:58:18.788
Do me a favor. Love me less.

1003
00:58:20.164 --> 00:58:21.207
REPORTER: Congressman!

1004
00:58:21.290 --> 00:58:24.251
WOMAN: Are you concerned at all
about Congressman Baxter's tirade

1005
00:58:24.335 --> 00:58:26.063
and the adverse effects it may have
on your bill?

1006
00:58:26.087 --> 00:58:29.840
The day it rains and floods and
Congressman Baxter takes a ride on his ark,

1007
00:58:29.924 --> 00:58:31.926
that'll be the day I'll be concerned.
Thank you.

1008
00:58:32.009 --> 00:58:34.470
<i>(WAITING ON THE WORLD</i>
<i>TO CHANGE</i> PLAYING)

1009
00:58:35.930 --> 00:58:36.931
(BLEATING)

1010
00:58:37.014 --> 00:58:41.352
His name is Evan Baxter,
but now he goes by "New York's Noah,"

1011
00:58:41.435 --> 00:58:45.106
"Heaven's Evan,"
"The Weirdo with a Beardo."

1012
00:58:50.111 --> 00:58:53.781
Okay, guys. Watch it. Watch it.
Coming through. Watch your back.

1013
00:58:55.324 --> 00:58:59.120
Marty, will you comment on Congressman
Baxter's change of appearance?

1014
00:58:59.370 --> 00:59:03.207
Yes, his hair is long.
Yes, his beard is unshaven.

1015
00:59:03.290 --> 00:59:05.501
Are you equally stunned
by this man's appearance?

1016
00:59:11.924 --> 00:59:13.124
The way things go around here,

1017
00:59:13.175 --> 00:59:15.970
if he gets any crazier,
we may end up in the White House.

1018
00:59:16.303 --> 00:59:21.892
(REPORTER SPEAKING SPANISH)

1019
00:59:22.309 --> 00:59:24.979
Hey! No, no, no! That's my cup!

1020
00:59:26.522 --> 00:59:27.857
Whatever.

1021
00:59:48.669 --> 00:59:52.131
<i>He's filling the boat
with two of every kind of animal.</i>

1022
00:59:52.214 --> 00:59:55.509
<i>Still to be collected,
two giraffes, two elephants</i>

1023
00:59:56.635 --> 00:59:58.471
<i>and one more jackass.</i>

1024
01:00:01.682 --> 01:00:04.143
- What an idiot.
- He's a mook.

1025
01:00:04.226 --> 01:00:05.644
Jerks.

1026
01:00:06.395 --> 01:00:09.023
Don't worry about it, you guys.
Come on, eat up.

1027
01:00:09.106 --> 01:00:11.358
- Not hungry.
- Yeah, me neither.

1028
01:00:11.442 --> 01:00:13.736
You guys can't eat. I can't stop.

1029
01:00:13.819 --> 01:00:15.738
- Can I go to the bathroom?
- Me, too?

1030
01:00:15.821 --> 01:00:19.700
- Okay. Dylan, go with them. Please?
- Fine.

1031
01:00:22.411 --> 01:00:26.040
- Excuse me. Can I get a refill, please?
- Coming right up.

1032
01:00:27.124 --> 01:00:28.125
Thank you.

1033
01:00:28.209 --> 01:00:31.337
- Excuse me. Are you all right?
- Yeah.

1034
01:00:33.631 --> 01:00:37.051
- No. It's a long story.
- Well, I like stories.

1035
01:00:37.968 --> 01:00:41.013
I'm considered a bit of
a storyteller myself.

1036
01:00:42.056 --> 01:00:45.184
My husband...
Have you heard of "New York's Noah"?

1037
01:00:46.769 --> 01:00:49.855
- The guy who's building the ark.
- That's him.

1038
01:00:49.939 --> 01:00:53.067
I love that story, Noah and the Ark.

1039
01:00:53.150 --> 01:00:54.795
You know, a lot of people miss the point
of that story.

1040
01:00:54.819 --> 01:00:57.404
They think it's about
God's wrath and anger.

1041
01:00:57.738 --> 01:01:02.034
- They love it when God gets angry.
- What is the story about, then? The ark?

1042
01:01:02.117 --> 01:01:07.498
Well, I think it's a love story
about believing in each other.

1043
01:01:07.581 --> 01:01:13.295
You know, the animals showed up in pairs.
They stood by each other, side by side,

1044
01:01:13.379 --> 01:01:17.675
just like Noah and his family.
Everybody entered the ark side by side.

1045
01:01:18.759 --> 01:01:21.637
But my husband says God told him to do it.

1046
01:01:23.430 --> 01:01:26.934
- What do you do with that?
- Sounds like an opportunity.

1047
01:01:29.937 --> 01:01:32.189
Let me ask you something.

1048
01:01:32.273 --> 01:01:36.026
If someone prays for patience,
you think God gives them patience?

1049
01:01:36.110 --> 01:01:39.405
Or does he give them
the opportunity to be patient?

1050
01:01:41.115 --> 01:01:43.176
If they pray for courage,
does God give them courage,

1051
01:01:43.200 --> 01:01:46.537
or does he give them opportunities
to be courageous?

1052
01:01:47.997 --> 01:01:51.542
If someone prayed
for their family to be closer,

1053
01:01:51.625 --> 01:01:55.337
you think God zaps them
with warm, fuzzy feelings?

1054
01:01:55.421 --> 01:01:58.883
Or does he give them opportunities
to love each other?

1055
01:01:59.800 --> 01:02:00.968
(GASPS QUIETLY)

1056
01:02:01.051 --> 01:02:05.139
Well, I got to run.
A lot of people to serve. Enjoy.

1057
01:02:12.146 --> 01:02:15.250
<i>JON: Guess this comes as no surprise to
those who remember his campaign promise,</i>

1058
01:02:15.274 --> 01:02:17.026
<i>"I will lower taxes,</i>

1059
01:02:17.484 --> 01:02:19.653
<i>"go crazy and build a gigantic ark."</i>

1060
01:02:19.778 --> 01:02:20.779
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

1061
01:02:27.703 --> 01:02:29.705
JOAN: Oh, my gosh.

1062
01:02:34.543 --> 01:02:36.587
- JOAN: Evan!
- Dad?

1063
01:02:36.670 --> 01:02:38.797
- Honey!
- Dad?

1064
01:02:38.881 --> 01:02:41.050
You guys, I'm up here.

1065
01:02:56.357 --> 01:02:57.358
(LAUGHING)

1066
01:02:57.816 --> 01:02:59.818
- Rough week?
- JORDAN: You look really funny.

1067
01:02:59.902 --> 01:03:03.238
- You look really old.
- Yeah, well, he is really old.

1068
01:03:04.990 --> 01:03:07.534
- Why'd you come back?
- It was the kids.

1069
01:03:07.618 --> 01:03:10.621
- Tell him, guys.
- We like you better as the crazy guy.

1070
01:03:10.704 --> 01:03:13.040
You spend time with us
and you're home a lot more.

1071
01:03:13.123 --> 01:03:16.251
Just, please don't make us do
the dance anymore.

1072
01:03:33.227 --> 01:03:34.228
(SIGHING)

1073
01:03:37.356 --> 01:03:41.819
I don't know what's going on,
or what you're going through,

1074
01:03:42.569 --> 01:03:48.242
but we got into this as a family
and we're gonna get out of it as a family,

1075
01:03:49.159 --> 01:03:50.828
side by side.

1076
01:03:58.252 --> 01:04:01.672
But, Evan, we have to talk about the ark.
It has to come down.

1077
01:04:01.755 --> 01:04:04.633
- I can't do that.
- You don't have a choice.

1078
01:04:05.009 --> 01:04:08.429
JOAN: Congressman Long went to the city.
There's a laundry list of code violations.

1079
01:04:08.595 --> 01:04:11.015
You have until September 22
to take it down,

1080
01:04:11.098 --> 01:04:13.017
or they'll take it down and arrest you.

1081
01:04:13.100 --> 01:04:16.603
- September 22. That's the day of the flood.
- Mom! Dad! Come here!

1082
01:04:22.985 --> 01:04:25.279
(ANIMALS CALLING)

1083
01:04:41.754 --> 01:04:44.214
Don't you dare take that ark down.

1084
01:04:46.800 --> 01:04:48.677
How are we gonna do this?

1085
01:04:48.761 --> 01:04:51.013
There's no way the five
of us can finish on time.

1086
01:04:51.096 --> 01:04:53.140
We don't have money to hire anybody else.

1087
01:04:53.223 --> 01:04:54.475
(ALPACA CRYING)

1088
01:04:58.270 --> 01:05:00.230
Is that a llama with a hammer?

1089
01:05:00.314 --> 01:05:04.401
An alpaca. They rarely spit at people
unless frightened or abused.

1090
01:05:06.236 --> 01:05:08.197
Let's finish this sucker.

1091
01:05:09.615 --> 01:05:10.775
<i>(READY FOR A MIRACLE</i> PLAYING)

1092
01:05:11.658 --> 01:05:12.701
(ELEPHANT TRUMPETING)

1093
01:05:12.785 --> 01:05:13.911
Come on, let's go.

1094
01:05:13.994 --> 01:05:15.472
<i>WOMAN:
No one knows where they came from</i>

1095
01:05:15.496 --> 01:05:17.348
<i>or how the congressman is getting them
to do it,</i>

1096
01:05:17.372 --> 01:05:23.253
<i>but, two by two, animals of all kinds are
working with Godspeed to build this ark.</i>

1097
01:05:23.337 --> 01:05:24.838
Thank you.

1098
01:05:24.922 --> 01:05:28.133
If this flood really does happen,
"Evan help us."

1099
01:05:29.760 --> 01:05:31.512
Hey! A little help?

1100
01:05:35.265 --> 01:05:36.308
Thanks.

1101
01:05:37.684 --> 01:05:38.685
JOAN: Here it is, hon.

1102
01:05:39.019 --> 01:05:40.020
(MONKEY GIBBERING)

1103
01:05:40.104 --> 01:05:42.856
Perfect. Thanks.

1104
01:05:46.735 --> 01:05:48.237
Hold it right there.

1105
01:05:48.320 --> 01:05:51.907
This is Ed Carson coming to you live
from New York Noah's construction site,

1106
01:05:51.990 --> 01:05:57.079
where we are unable to leave the news van
due to hazardous conditions outside.

1107
01:06:00.207 --> 01:06:01.208
- High five.
- High five.

1108
01:06:01.291 --> 01:06:02.292
Good job.

1109
01:06:02.960 --> 01:06:04.670
Hey, putty tat.

1110
01:06:06.964 --> 01:06:08.632
(SHRIEKING)

1111
01:06:08.715 --> 01:06:11.552
Go, go, go! He tried to eat me!

1112
01:06:11.844 --> 01:06:14.555
Dylan! Jordan! Check it out!
Your mom's building an ark!

1113
01:06:14.638 --> 01:06:15.973
Let's do the dance.

1114
01:06:16.056 --> 01:06:18.058
JOAN: No, please, no.

1115
01:06:19.643 --> 01:06:20.644
(HONKING)

1116
01:06:20.727 --> 01:06:22.705
WOMAN 1: Well, where did
the animals come from, then?

1117
01:06:22.729 --> 01:06:25.375
WOMAN 2: Please. It's a trick.
WOMAN 3: It's a circus is what it is.

1118
01:06:25.399 --> 01:06:28.485
Wild animals running amok
in suburban Virginia.

1119
01:06:28.569 --> 01:06:32.406
With all these species,
what's being done about the feces?

1120
01:06:38.412 --> 01:06:43.667
Evan Baxter! You have gone from newsman
to congressman to caveman.

1121
01:06:43.750 --> 01:06:46.545
What makes you so sure God chose you?

1122
01:06:47.504 --> 01:06:49.256
He chose all of us.

1123
01:06:58.682 --> 01:07:00.559
Time to wash up, you guys.

1124
01:07:07.149 --> 01:07:08.358
Thanks.

1125
01:07:11.778 --> 01:07:13.280
You want some?

1126
01:07:33.508 --> 01:07:36.637
RITA: Why couldn't
the man just buy a Corvette?

1127
01:07:36.720 --> 01:07:40.933
Well, well, well. There they are.
It is good to see you guys.

1128
01:07:41.016 --> 01:07:46.063
It's good to see you! Your hair looks great.
It's very regal. Man, I love your hair!

1129
01:07:46.146 --> 01:07:47.731
And you're still sucking up.

1130
01:07:47.814 --> 01:07:49.858
- So, why are you here?
- Long locked us out.

1131
01:07:49.942 --> 01:07:50.943
He can't do that.

1132
01:07:51.026 --> 01:07:53.266
I mean, I've been suspended,
but I'm still a congressman.

1133
01:07:53.320 --> 01:07:55.572
- Rita, tell him what you know.
- Tell me what?

1134
01:07:55.656 --> 01:07:58.408
I smelled a rat
the second we got that office.

1135
01:07:58.492 --> 01:08:00.577
You don't get an office like that
for nothing.

1136
01:08:00.661 --> 01:08:04.957
- So I had the stalker here do some research.
- Okay, Eugene, talk.

1137
01:08:05.082 --> 01:08:07.292
Prestige Crest used to be federal lands,

1138
01:08:07.501 --> 01:08:10.003
but what's interesting is
how it got into private hands.

1139
01:08:10.295 --> 01:08:12.631
Congressman Long got the approval
to build a dam

1140
01:08:12.714 --> 01:08:15.634
and then passed out the surrounding lands
to a group of private investors.

1141
01:08:15.717 --> 01:08:17.111
Now, the locals fought
this thing for years.

1142
01:08:17.135 --> 01:08:19.447
They said Long and his developer buddies
were cutting corners,

1143
01:08:19.471 --> 01:08:21.723
like skipping important building code
checkpoints.

1144
01:08:21.807 --> 01:08:24.953
And with the land use bill, he's gonna do
the same thing with the national parks.

1145
01:08:24.977 --> 01:08:28.647
So, you stand by and shake your pom-poms
while Long and his buddies get rich.

1146
01:08:28.730 --> 01:08:30.857
What can we do? I'm suspended.

1147
01:08:30.941 --> 01:08:34.361
Go back to the Hill and show them
that you can and will fight this bill.

1148
01:08:34.444 --> 01:08:37.406
You guys, I'm sorry. I can't do that.
I have to get back to the ark.

1149
01:08:37.489 --> 01:08:39.157
The ark? All right. Okay.

1150
01:08:39.241 --> 01:08:41.159
- God told you to build an ark?
- Yes.

1151
01:08:41.243 --> 01:08:44.288
But did he tell you to make your friends
believe in you and follow you here

1152
01:08:44.371 --> 01:08:48.583
so you can make us look stupid?
'Cause I go to church every Sunday.

1153
01:08:48.667 --> 01:08:50.919
Okay, every other Sunday.

1154
01:08:51.003 --> 01:08:54.464
I've been to church!
And that does not sound like God to me.

1155
01:08:54.548 --> 01:08:56.925
Rita, I know
that this doesn't make any sense.

1156
01:08:57.009 --> 01:08:59.678
I just want you to trust me.
You just have to have faith.

1157
01:08:59.761 --> 01:09:04.391
Evan, faith will not fight this bill.
The CINPLAN vote is today!

1158
01:09:04.474 --> 01:09:08.186
If we're going to stop this thing,
you need to get down to Capitol Hill now!

1159
01:09:08.270 --> 01:09:12.566
- Otherwise, it's impossible!
- Dad, Dad, I think it's done.

1160
01:10:11.124 --> 01:10:15.379
What in the world?
I can't even get my cat to use the litter box.

1161
01:10:56.795 --> 01:11:01.216
It's September 22, and
we're all still here.

1162
01:11:01.299 --> 01:11:02.801
Awkward!

1163
01:11:02.884 --> 01:11:06.263
People! The flood is imminent!

1164
01:11:06.346 --> 01:11:11.476
- Board the ark! Save yourselves!
- MAN: Get down, you fool!

1165
01:11:11.977 --> 01:11:15.939
Listen to me! The time has come!

1166
01:11:16.022 --> 01:11:20.110
No, Captain Ahab! Your time has come!

1167
01:11:20.193 --> 01:11:21.319
(ALL LAUGHING)

1168
01:11:21.403 --> 01:11:26.116
Yeah, Baxter! The weather's 70 and sunny
with a chance of crazy!

1169
01:11:26.199 --> 01:11:27.659
(ALL GIGGLING)

1170
01:11:29.369 --> 01:11:31.455
(RUMBLING)

1171
01:11:31.538 --> 01:11:37.586
- Do you hear that? The rains are upon us!
- Dad, I don't think that's the rains.

1172
01:11:38.879 --> 01:11:40.046
(SIREN BLARING)

1173
01:11:42.007 --> 01:11:44.634
MAN: Hey, Baxter! Kiss your ark goodbye!

1174
01:11:57.230 --> 01:11:59.566
- Where is he?
- On the boat, sir.

1175
01:12:00.233 --> 01:12:02.360
Give me a minute.
Lets see if I can convince "Noah"

1176
01:12:02.444 --> 01:12:04.613
that the world doesn't have to end today.

1177
01:12:08.325 --> 01:12:11.328
I gotta hand it to you,
this is quite the show.

1178
01:12:11.411 --> 01:12:14.456
According to my source,
the show hasn't even started yet.

1179
01:12:14.539 --> 01:12:16.208
Still expecting the big flood.

1180
01:12:16.291 --> 01:12:18.603
You know, voters don't respond
to the gloom and doom stuff.

1181
01:12:18.627 --> 01:12:21.856
- They like a more positive message.
- Like the one you're sending with your bill?

1182
01:12:21.880 --> 01:12:23.840
How much did you make off of all this land?

1183
01:12:23.924 --> 01:12:27.177
You are destroying
our national parks for profit.

1184
01:12:27.260 --> 01:12:29.197
You have a problem
with somebody taking a little profit?

1185
01:12:29.221 --> 01:12:30.764
It's called business, son.

1186
01:12:30.847 --> 01:12:33.409
So if I need to get a message out there,
or get a congressman elected

1187
01:12:33.433 --> 01:12:37.479
there are people who pay for it, and yes,
those people want this bill to happen

1188
01:12:37.562 --> 01:12:41.650
and, by God, it's gonna happen.
Now you look down there.

1189
01:12:42.275 --> 01:12:44.027
Those are the wolves, son.

1190
01:12:44.110 --> 01:12:47.197
I'm gonna give you one last chance.
Take down this boat.

1191
01:12:47.280 --> 01:12:51.034
I'm giving you one last chance. Repent.

1192
01:12:52.285 --> 01:12:56.206
Such a shame. You had possibilities.

1193
01:12:56.289 --> 01:13:00.168
But you want to stop progress
to save the Earth. Go for it.

1194
01:13:00.252 --> 01:13:03.213
Good luck getting a tree
to come to the polls.

1195
01:13:08.134 --> 01:13:09.636
Take it down.

1196
01:13:16.935 --> 01:13:20.146
<i>This is a court order
approving the demolition of this boat!</i>

1197
01:13:20.230 --> 01:13:23.233
<i>Evacuate immediately!
You have three minutes!</i>

1198
01:13:25.902 --> 01:13:30.115
Honey. We have to go.
They're going to destroy the boat.

1199
01:13:30.865 --> 01:13:32.033
No.

1200
01:13:33.076 --> 01:13:34.995
It can't end this way.

1201
01:13:36.329 --> 01:13:40.333
Is it too much to ask
for a little precipitation?

1202
01:13:41.501 --> 01:13:45.255
Honey, maybe God didn't mean
a literal flood.

1203
01:13:45.338 --> 01:13:50.635
Maybe he meant a flood of knowledge
or emotion or awareness.

1204
01:13:50.719 --> 01:13:52.304
If that's true,

1205
01:13:53.221 --> 01:13:56.433
I am going to be so pissed.

1206
01:13:56.516 --> 01:13:57.767
<i>Two minutes!</i>

1207
01:13:57.851 --> 01:14:01.271
<i>Get off the boat now
or you will be removed by force.</i>

1208
01:14:01.354 --> 01:14:04.899
Evan, you did it. You built the ark.

1209
01:14:04.983 --> 01:14:07.944
- That's all you were asked to do, right?
- No.

1210
01:14:08.028 --> 01:14:12.240
There's something else.
Something's going to happen. I can feel it.

1211
01:14:12.324 --> 01:14:15.118
Yeah, what's gonna happen is
tear gas and a wrecking ball.

1212
01:14:15.201 --> 01:14:17.203
Evan, think of the kids.

1213
01:14:18.288 --> 01:14:19.706
<i>One minute!</i>

1214
01:14:21.916 --> 01:14:25.503
- Dad, whatever you say, I'm with you.
- Yeah, me, too.

1215
01:14:25.587 --> 01:14:27.672
Me, too.
But can we keep some of the animals?

1216
01:14:27.756 --> 01:14:30.008
I like the alpaca. He spits.

1217
01:14:34.512 --> 01:14:37.849
You're right. We did it. We built the boat.

1218
01:14:38.224 --> 01:14:39.225
Yeah.

1219
01:14:40.226 --> 01:14:42.646
Let's go. Let's go, guys. Come on.

1220
01:14:55.742 --> 01:14:57.452
EVAN: Well, I guess they don't want to go.

1221
01:14:57.535 --> 01:15:00.622
- It's their instinct.
- What do you mean, hon?

1222
01:15:00.705 --> 01:15:05.460
Some animals know when weather's coming.
When they feel it coming, they sit.

1223
01:15:11.299 --> 01:15:12.884
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1224
01:15:13.593 --> 01:15:14.719
Joan!

1225
01:15:18.056 --> 01:15:19.432
(THUNDER CLAPPING)

1226
01:15:24.104 --> 01:15:26.648
<i>Okay. Time's up! We're coming in!</i>

1227
01:15:26.731 --> 01:15:29.943
Get that ball in position!
We're clearing them out!

1228
01:15:36.741 --> 01:15:38.618
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1229
01:15:40.870 --> 01:15:44.165
Is that rain? It's raining.

1230
01:15:44.249 --> 01:15:46.793
Lucky guess, Baxter. Lucky guess.

1231
01:15:48.294 --> 01:15:49.295
(THUNDER CLAPPING)

1232
01:16:03.309 --> 01:16:07.564
Looks like the drought's finally over.
Good news, eh, Congressman?

1233
01:16:07.647 --> 01:16:09.816
Yeah. Good news.

1234
01:16:12.277 --> 01:16:17.824
Everybody! Please! Get on the ark!

1235
01:16:19.826 --> 01:16:21.327
Go to the car!

1236
01:16:21.411 --> 01:16:25.498
Please! Everyone! On the ark!

1237
01:16:25.582 --> 01:16:28.918
Cover me up! Keep me dry!
Cover me up! Keep me dry!

1238
01:16:29.002 --> 01:16:33.006
Who's crazy now, huh?
Look at us all squishing!

1239
01:16:41.139 --> 01:16:43.975
- It kind of stopped raining.
- Is that it?

1240
01:16:44.058 --> 01:16:46.478
What did I tell you? It's fine. It's over.

1241
01:16:46.561 --> 01:16:48.646
Hey, Ahab! This is it?

1242
01:16:49.272 --> 01:16:51.816
Your God experiencing
a little water shortage?

1243
01:16:51.900 --> 01:16:52.942
(ALL LAUGHING)

1244
01:16:53.026 --> 01:16:56.654
It would appear Evan Baxter
was right about the rain,

1245
01:16:56.738 --> 01:17:00.241
with a slight miscalculation
as to the quantity.

1246
01:17:04.329 --> 01:17:07.540
- Something's wrong.
- Honey, the clouds are moving away.

1247
01:17:07.624 --> 01:17:10.627
No, no. No, this isn't right.

1248
01:17:11.461 --> 01:17:14.839
Evan, even if it kept raining,
it's not like it could cause a flood in a day.

1249
01:17:14.923 --> 01:17:20.178
But today is the day! It has to be.
This just doesn't make any sense!

1250
01:17:22.138 --> 01:17:24.349
- Wait a second.
- What is it?

1251
01:17:24.432 --> 01:17:28.102
Marty said that Long cut corners,
violated building codes.

1252
01:17:28.186 --> 01:17:30.730
- What are you talking about?
- The lake, Long Lake.

1253
01:17:30.814 --> 01:17:34.734
It's named after him.
It's the lake! It's the lake!

1254
01:17:47.914 --> 01:17:49.249
Oh, no.

1255
01:17:51.084 --> 01:17:55.797
Get on the ark! Everyone, on the ark now!

1256
01:17:55.880 --> 01:17:57.715
I think we should get on the ark.

1257
01:17:57.799 --> 01:18:00.635
I agree.
I think we should get on the ark also.

1258
01:18:00.718 --> 01:18:04.347
I'm cold. I'm wet. I'm going home.

1259
01:18:11.271 --> 01:18:13.439
Ladies first! Move!

1260
01:18:21.322 --> 01:18:24.951
Oh, my God. This is happening.
This is really happening.

1261
01:18:26.035 --> 01:18:29.372
Holy... Get everyone on the ark now!

1262
01:18:29.455 --> 01:18:32.083
Get on the ark now! Let's go!
Get on the ark! Let's go!

1263
01:18:32.166 --> 01:18:35.044
Go, go, go! Get on the ark!

1264
01:18:35.128 --> 01:18:36.629
(ALL SCREAMING)

1265
01:18:36.713 --> 01:18:40.842
Go, go, go! On the ark! Go, go, go!

1266
01:18:40.925 --> 01:18:43.386
All right, boys! Let's go! Let's go!

1267
01:18:43.469 --> 01:18:47.015
We're gonna need a bigger boat.
Stay here with the kids.

1268
01:18:56.149 --> 01:18:57.984
Come on, Rita!

1269
01:18:58.067 --> 01:19:02.238
Everyone, up the ramp! Onto the deck!
Come on! Hurry, hurry, hurry!

1270
01:19:02.322 --> 01:19:06.159
- Dylan, get back inside! It's too dangerous.
- No, Dad. I told you, I'm with you.

1271
01:19:10.538 --> 01:19:13.333
EVAN: Careful, everyone.
In the ark! In the ark!

1272
01:19:13.416 --> 01:19:15.501
Watch your step! Up the ramp, everybody!

1273
01:19:23.760 --> 01:19:26.120
- Guys, help me with the door!
- Get the door! Get the door!

1274
01:19:33.186 --> 01:19:35.104
(ALL SCREAMING)

1275
01:20:08.888 --> 01:20:10.431
Guys! Guys!

1276
01:20:43.423 --> 01:20:45.174
Everybody hang on!

1277
01:20:55.435 --> 01:20:56.519
(ROARING)

1278
01:20:56.602 --> 01:20:58.771
You guys all right? You okay?

1279
01:20:59.397 --> 01:21:01.000
<i>MAN (OVER TV):
There's been a flood at Prestige Crest</i>

1280
01:21:01.024 --> 01:21:03.192
<i>and you're seeing live images
of New York Noah's ark</i>

1281
01:21:03.276 --> 01:21:06.487
<i>caught in the storm surge
and heading towards Memorial Bridge!</i>

1282
01:21:14.328 --> 01:21:16.873
WOMAN: We're going to crash!
MAN: Turn this thing around!

1283
01:21:16.956 --> 01:21:19.792
MAN 2: We're not gonna make it!
MAN 3: Save us, Baxter!

1284
01:21:31.512 --> 01:21:36.100
I command thee halt! Stop! Whoa!

1285
01:21:36.184 --> 01:21:37.852
WOMAN: It's not working!

1286
01:21:38.644 --> 01:21:41.397
How about a little help here?

1287
01:21:57.663 --> 01:21:58.664
(SCREAMING)

1288
01:22:25.817 --> 01:22:26.859
(SCREAMING)

1289
01:22:27.235 --> 01:22:29.797
What do you mean there was water damage?
It rained for ten minutes.

1290
01:22:29.821 --> 01:22:31.614
That is not possible.

1291
01:22:40.164 --> 01:22:41.165
(EXCLAIMING)

1292
01:22:41.249 --> 01:22:43.126
- I love you guys.
- All right.

1293
01:22:43.209 --> 01:22:44.460
- Seriously.
- Okay, I got it.

1294
01:22:44.544 --> 01:22:45.670
- I love you.
- Thank you.

1295
01:22:45.753 --> 01:22:47.046
(EAGLE CRYING)

1296
01:23:03.146 --> 01:23:07.733
LONG: All those in favor of the Public
Land Act, please signify by saying, "Aye."

1297
01:23:08.067 --> 01:23:10.027
(CLAMORING)

1298
01:23:14.824 --> 01:23:16.117
Good God!

1299
01:23:25.126 --> 01:23:26.919
(ALL YELLING)

1300
01:23:51.444 --> 01:23:52.862
I think we can walk from here.

1301
01:23:52.945 --> 01:23:54.530
(SIRENS BLARING)

1302
01:24:11.130 --> 01:24:15.760
Hello, Congressman.
Mind if I park my boat here for a little while?

1303
01:24:16.844 --> 01:24:18.930
- But how...
- The dam, Congressman.

1304
01:24:19.013 --> 01:24:22.558
Your reservoir ruptured.
Prestige Crest, it's all gone.

1305
01:24:22.642 --> 01:24:25.186
No. They said that couldn't happen.

1306
01:24:26.229 --> 01:24:27.939
I never thought this...

1307
01:24:28.814 --> 01:24:33.694
You. You did this to me.
You set me up, you crazy son of a...

1308
01:24:33.778 --> 01:24:36.948
(MONKEYS SCREECHING)

1309
01:24:37.031 --> 01:24:39.367
Wow. That is disgusting.

1310
01:24:39.825 --> 01:24:41.244
If that comes out your front,

1311
01:24:41.327 --> 01:24:44.747
I don't even want to know
what's coming out the back.

1312
01:24:46.499 --> 01:24:47.917
(SNARLING)

1313
01:24:48.000 --> 01:24:50.544
Don't look down, Congressman,
but the wolves are here,

1314
01:24:50.628 --> 01:24:54.548
although I wouldn't worry so much
about these wolves as those.

1315
01:25:02.848 --> 01:25:04.225
<i>Gesundheit.</i>

1316
01:25:16.320 --> 01:25:19.949
<i>MAN 1: As you can see behind me,
New York Noah's prediction came true.</i>

1317
01:25:20.032 --> 01:25:22.535
<i>WOMAN: The vote of the Land Act Bill
has been suspended,</i>

1318
01:25:22.618 --> 01:25:25.454
<i>pending investigation of Congressman Long
for profiteering...</i>

1319
01:25:25.538 --> 01:25:28.499
MAN 2: Of course now, the question is,
how will these animals be returned

1320
01:25:28.582 --> 01:25:30.126
to their natural habitats?

1321
01:25:30.209 --> 01:25:34.088
Something tells me, if God got them here,
he can probably get them home.

1322
01:25:34.171 --> 01:25:37.216
<i>WOMAN 2: The House will undoubtedly
reinstate Congressman Baxter</i>

1323
01:25:37.300 --> 01:25:39.051
<i>when it reconvenes in the morning.</i>

1324
01:25:39.135 --> 01:25:42.972
<i>Until then, there is a lot to be done here
on Capitol Hill.</i>

1325
01:25:43.055 --> 01:25:45.141
JORDAN: How's Buster doing?
EVAN: Come on, Buster.

1326
01:25:45.224 --> 01:25:47.601
JOAN: No, come on. Come on!
RYAN: Come on!

1327
01:25:47.685 --> 01:25:49.538
EVAN: These too heavy? It's all right?
JORDAN: No, it's fine.

1328
01:25:49.562 --> 01:25:51.981
- RYAN: He can't keep up.
- I know, sweetie!

1329
01:25:52.064 --> 01:25:55.276
All right.
What do you say we take a little break?

1330
01:25:55.359 --> 01:25:57.045
We've only been walking
for, like, five minutes, Dad.

1331
01:25:57.069 --> 01:26:00.281
Well, five on, five off.
Life is about balance, right?

1332
01:26:00.364 --> 01:26:01.717
- How about some sandwiches?
- Okay.

1333
01:26:01.741 --> 01:26:04.618
- Who wants sandwiches? Let's do it!
- RYAN: I get first dibs!

1334
01:26:04.702 --> 01:26:06.996
Everyone but Buster
is going to get a sandwich.

1335
01:26:07.079 --> 01:26:11.459
You do not get a sandwich! You're a dog
and you do not get a sandwich!

1336
01:26:11.542 --> 01:26:14.754
Buster is part of the family now.
You're just gonna have to get used to it.

1337
01:26:14.837 --> 01:26:16.672
Poor Buster!

1338
01:26:17.423 --> 01:26:20.509
Honey, come here.
Sweetheart, be careful. Come here.

1339
01:26:20.593 --> 01:26:22.511
- Hey, hon, save me one, okay?
- Okay.

1340
01:26:22.595 --> 01:26:24.347
I'll be right back.

1341
01:26:32.355 --> 01:26:33.731
- Hey.
- Hey.

1342
01:26:35.608 --> 01:26:37.568
What are you doing here?

1343
01:26:37.860 --> 01:26:40.279
Just hanging out with some old friends.

1344
01:26:40.363 --> 01:26:43.657
You knew all along, didn't you?
You knew the dam was unstable.

1345
01:26:43.741 --> 01:26:47.578
If it hadn't been for the ark,
my family, the neighbors...

1346
01:26:47.661 --> 01:26:51.457
- I fought you every step of the way.
- Yes, but you did it.

1347
01:26:52.458 --> 01:26:57.004
So, you had nothing to do with the flood?
Like where the ark landed exactly?

1348
01:26:57.088 --> 01:27:00.549
I gave you a little shove at the end.
Sue me.

1349
01:27:00.633 --> 01:27:01.634
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

1350
01:27:03.135 --> 01:27:06.847
You did good, son. You changed the world.

1351
01:27:06.931 --> 01:27:09.600
- No, no, I didn't.
- Well, let's see.

1352
01:27:09.683 --> 01:27:13.771
Spending time with your family,
making them very happy.

1353
01:27:13.854 --> 01:27:17.149
- Gave that dog a home.
- Right. So?

1354
01:27:17.817 --> 01:27:19.527
So?

1355
01:27:19.610 --> 01:27:21.737
How do we change the world?

1356
01:27:23.322 --> 01:27:26.742
One act of random kindness at a time.

1357
01:27:26.826 --> 01:27:31.372
One act of random kindness.

1358
01:27:36.502 --> 01:27:37.837
It's time.

1359
01:27:39.880 --> 01:27:41.382
Do the dance.

1360
01:27:42.842 --> 01:27:44.510
Care to join me?

1361
01:27:50.391 --> 01:27:51.392
(CHUCKLING)

1362
01:28:06.490 --> 01:28:07.491
(DOVE COOING)

1363
01:28:41.025 --> 01:28:45.738
I now issue a new commandment,
"Thou shalt do the dance."

1364
01:28:45.946 --> 01:28:47.946
<i>(GONNA MAKE YOU SWEAT,</i>
<i>EVERYBODY DANCE NOW</i> PLAYING)

1365
01:29:41.794 --> 01:29:43.295
(LIP-SYNCING)

1366
01:29:48.050 --> 01:29:51.178
Stop it! This is stupid!

1367
01:29:51.262 --> 01:29:54.473
That's awful dancing! You better stop!

1368
01:30:00.312 --> 01:30:02.064
(LIP-SYNCING)

1369
01:30:17.997 --> 01:30:18.998
(LIP-SYNCING)

1370
01:30:27.381 --> 01:30:29.008
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

1371
01:30:32.761 --> 01:30:34.921
<i>MAN 1: Ladies and gentlemen,
you don't have to go home.</i>

1372
01:30:34.972 --> 01:30:37.600
<i>You just have to go. We are wrapped.</i>

1373
01:30:37.683 --> 01:30:40.394
<i>MAN 2: We're wrapped.
We love you. Thank you.</i>

1374
01:30:41.186 --> 01:30:43.188
<i>(READY FOR A MIRACLE</i> PLAYING)

